cs.CC, cs.DS, cs.GT, cs.AI, cs.CG

This paper deals with the computational complexity of a game played over a partially ordered set (poset), which involves graph theory and combinatorial game theory. Therefore, cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) are the most likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves game theory, which suggests cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) as another possible sub-category. The paper also mentions the existence of polynomial time algorithms for certain restricted classes of poset games, which suggests cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper involves a reduction from a PSPACE-complete game, which suggests cs.CG (Computational Geometry) as a possible sub-category.
